text: Colligny-Maizery is a French commune. It is in the Moselle department. The municipality was created on 1 June 2016 and consists of the former communes of Colligny (the seat) and Maizery.Arrêté préfectoral 29 April 2016 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Moselle
title: Colligny-Maizery
